## Release v0.9.5

### Misc

- Added text to title screen to check out the pdf manual with the GitHub project location to Void-Merchants
- Added sound when hitting an enemy
- Added a score after finishing the game based on the players credits + value stored of goods and upgrades - negative-credits
  - This change hopefully adds some purpose actually play the game and not try to abuse some mechanics because of the missing boss at the end
  - loading the game increases negative-credits by 100 to give an incentive to load as little as possible for score hunters
- Added explosion when drone was killed
- Added explosion on the death screen

- Changed game balancing
  - Overall decreased storage to make it more important what to pick up and harder to get all upgrades
    - Player ship now calculates storage based on: mid(3, ceil(tier * 1.5), 8) (min 3, max 8)
    - Attack drones now calculates storage based on: ceil(tier * 0.5) (min 1, max 3)
    - Cargo drones now calculates storage based on: tier * 2 (min 2, max 6)
  - Made difficulty spike a little bit flater and decreased overall difficulty a little bit
- Changed void creature dialouge to make the game slightly more coherent
- Improved and updated the manual

- Fixed a bug where the player ship could go out of screen when approaching the trading station
- Fixed some small sound issues
- Fixed version to make more sense. It is now 0.x.x now before the 1.0 release

- Removed showing life and shields as 3 symbols when < 4 to get back some needed code tokens

## Files included

- `void-merchants.p8` — PICO-8 standard cart in clear text format
- `void-merchants.p8.png` — PICO-8 cart image
- `void-merchants_linux.zip` — Linux binaries
- `void-merchants_windows.zip` — Windows binaries
- `void-merchants_raspi.zip` — Raspberry Pi binaries
- `void-merchants_osx.zip` — macOS binaries
- `manual.pdf` — Manual for this release
- `LICENSE.txt` — Licensing information